FBIS4-31641 "dreeu114_p_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 POLAND National Security Head Resigns; Successor Named National Security Head Resigns; Successor Named LD1306173194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 GMT 13 Jun 94 LD1306173194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network Polish BFN [Text] This evening Minister Jerzy Milewski asked President Lech Walesa to release him from the duties of National Defense Committee secretary and the responsibility of heading the National Security Bureau attached to the president's chancellery, which is legally linked to them. Lech Walesa has accepted the resignation and appointed Henryk Goryszewski to these posts, and simultaneously appointed him also secretary of state in the Chancellery of the President of the Polish Republic.
